items.title: Deprecation warning due to invalid escape sequences.
items.body:
Deprecation warning due to invalid escape sequences. Using raw strings or escaping them again helps in resolving this. Check https://github.com/asottile/pyupgrade/ for automatic fix of this.

```
find . -iname '*.py' | grep -Ev 'rdf4|tool' | xargs -P4 -I{} python3.8 -Wall -m py_compile {}
./tests/unit/test_utils.py:303: DeprecationWarning: invalid escape sequence \.
  '%s\.[0-9A-Fa-f]{8}$' % filename,
```

items.title: FileExistError when running script on windows, runs fine on linux
items.body:
My application uses the ibmcloudsql package installed from pip. Here I list the version of the various related packages:

* ibm-cos-sdk            2.4.4
* ibm-cos-sdk-core       2.4.4
* ibm-cos-sdk-s3transfer 2.4.4
* ibmcloudsql            0.2.23

The application calls run_sql from a SQLquery  instance.
While running run_sql the error occurs where it tries to rename a file in the local temp directory, generating the FileExistsError. 
I tried to remove the existing file from the debugger after the error occurred and it gives a permission error. 
Running the application from an administrator console doesn't solve the issue.
It looks to me that the temporary file to be removed is still opened when it tries to remove it.

Tested on 2 different pcs with windows 7 and windows 10. 
The linux version (packages installed with pip at the same version number) runs fine

items.title: .travis.yml: The 'sudo' tag is now deprecated in Travis CI
items.body:
[Travis are now recommending removing the __sudo__ tag](https://blog.travis-ci.com/2018-11-19-required-linux-infrastructure-migration).

"_If you currently specify __sudo: false__ in your __.travis.yml__, we recommend removing that configuration_"
